---
layout: default
---
.row-fluid
  .col-lg-12
    .page-header.jumbo
      %h1
        %i.fa.fa-download
        Download
      %p.lead Please feel free to choose a distribution most appropriate for you.
.row
  .col-lg-6
    %h3
      %i.fa.fa-gear
      Binary Distribution
    %p
      This a
      %strong ready to run
      distribution of PerfCake. All you need is an installation of
      %a{:href => "http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/"} Java SE 8
      or later (look for JDK).
    %p
      This distribution format is the latest released version. It is based on the master branch in the
      = succeed "." do
        %a{:href => "https://github.com/PerfCake/PerfCake"} source code repository on GitHub
    %p
      The binaries can be run on Linux, MacOS X and Windows platforms with
      %a{ :href => "http://java.com/en/download/index.jsp" } Java SE 8
      installed, both x86 and x86_64 architectures.
    %p
      %a.btn.btn-primary.btn-big{ :href=>"https://github.com/PerfCake/PerfCake/releases/download/v#{site.version}/perfcake-v#{site.version}-bin.tar.bz2" }
        %i.fa.fa-download
        Download #{site.version} Binary Distribution (tar.bz2) &raquo;
    %p
      %a.btn.btn-primary.btn-big{ :href=>"https://github.com/PerfCake/PerfCake/releases/download/v#{site.version}/perfcake-v#{site.version}-bin.tar.gz" }
        %i.fa.fa-download
        Download #{site.version} Binary Distribution (tar.gz) &raquo;
    %p
      %a.btn.btn-primary.btn-big{ :href=>"https://github.com/PerfCake/PerfCake/releases/download/v#{site.version}/perfcake-v#{site.version}-bin.zip" }
        %i.fa.fa-download
        Download #{site.version} Binary Distribution (zip) &raquo;
  .col-lg-6
    %h3
      %i.fa.fa-keyboard
      Source Code Distribution
    %p
      This a distribution of the
      %strong master branch
      directly from our
      = succeed "." do
        %a{:href => "https://github.com/PerfCake/PerfCake"} source code repository on GitHub
      This is recommended for advanced users.
    %p
      You might be interested in how to
      %a{ :href => "#{site.base_url}/quickstart" } compile and run
      this distribution.
    %p
      %a.btn.btn-primary.btn-big{ :href=>"https://github.com/PerfCake/PerfCake/archive/v#{site.version}.tar.gz" }
        %i.fa.fa-download
        Download #{site.version} Source Distribution (tar.gz) &raquo;
    %p
      %a.btn.btn-primary.btn-big{ :href=>"https://github.com/PerfCake/PerfCake/archive/v#{site.version}.zip" }
        %i.fa.fa-download
        Download #{site.version} Source Distribution (zip) &raquo;
    %p
      %a.btn.btn-primary.btn-big{ :href=>'https://github.com/PerfCake/PerfCake/archive/master.zip' }
        %i.fa.fa-download
        Download the Source Code from GitHub (zip) &raquo;
